You are a senior backend engineer. Build a backend + Telegram bot for a "Gym Accountability App".

### Tech Stack:
- Node.js with Express
- PostgreSQL (or Supabase)
- Prisma ORM
- Telegram Bot API (node-telegram-bot-api)

### Core Features:

1. User System:
   - Create user with Telegram ID
   - Store username, phone (optional)

2. Challenge System:
   - Create challenge
   - Join challenge via invite link
   - Store participants

3. Gym Location:
   - Each user can save a gym location (lat, lng)

4. Check-in Logic:
   - API receives user GPS coordinates
   - Check if within 100 meters of gym (use Haversine formula)
   - If user stays >= 40 mins → mark session complete

5. Telegram Bot Integration:
   - When user joins challenge → send welcome message
   - When user enters gym:
     - Send message to group:
       "Ajay just entered the gym 💪"
   - When session completed:
     - "Ajay completed today's workout 🔥"
   - When user misses:
     - "John skipped today 😴"

6. Scheduler (CRON):
   - Run daily check for missed workouts
   - Reset daily status

7. Leaderboard API:
   - Return ranked users based on completed days

---

### API Endpoints:
- POST /auth/login
- POST /challenge/create
- POST /challenge/join
- GET /challenge/:id
- POST /location/update
- POST /checkin
- GET /leaderboard/:challengeId

---

### Database Models:
User:
- id
- name
- telegramId
- gymLat
- gymLng

Challenge:
- id
- name
- daysPerWeek
- durationMinutes

Participant:
- userId
- challengeId
- streak
- completedDays

Checkin:
- userId
- challengeId
- startTime
- endTime
- status

---

### Telegram Bot:
- Initialize bot with token
- Listen for /start
- Map Telegram user to app user
- Send messages to group chat

---

### Important:
- Use Haversine formula for distance calculation
- Prevent duplicate check-ins
- Handle edge cases (user leaves early)
- Structure code cleanly (controllers, services, routes)

